31 Jul 2018 18:40








Termination methods used must possess a 0% chance of failure.
附加记录：    

Quibble with this, because the Foundation literally can't reach 0% exactly. Absolutely any method you can use to kill someone has to have a potential failure state of some probability, for any of a variety of reasons. Maybe the mechanism fails to operate properly. Maybe the method used isn't effective somehow. Maybe the individual has a random heretofore-unknown resistance to the method. Maybe the stars aligned and freak good luck keeps the method from being fatal (history is rife with stories of ). That last one in particular would be impossible to control unless the Foundation can literally control probability, and that's a power it really shouldn't be allowed to have.

But I think this opens up an avenue of creativity. What would the Foundation deem acceptably close to zero to be effective containment? How would they determine that? I think that would be a solid addition, especially since you have an object that deals with theoretically infinite possibilities.







